President Obama called Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas to discuss various issues, including Middle East peace. The President reaffirmed America's commitment to the objectives outlined by the Quartet and praised the efforts of King Abdullah of Jordan and his Foreign Minister Nasser Judeh in advancing dialogue between the parties. They also discussed the need for all parties to support the efforts that ended the recent fighting and the importance of the two-state solution. President Obama acknowledged Jordan's role in fostering direct discussions between Israel and the Palestinians. They also emphasized the need to build trust and avoid provocative actions that hinder progress. The leaders agreed to remain in close contact regarding these important matters.